      • createTestRevisitResource

        public static Resource createTestRevisitResource(String timestamp,
                                 int len,
                                 boolean withHeader)
                                          throws IOException
        Create a test revisit record referring unknown capture of content-length len. This is meant for pathological case. Use createTestRevisitResource(String, int, boolean) for regular case.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - 14-digit timestamp of capture
        len - original content-length
        withHeader - false for omitting HTTP header (simulates old revisit record).
        Returns:
        new Resource object.
        Throws:
        IOException - for unexpected I/O failure while buiding payload

      • createTestRevisitResource

        public static Resource createTestRevisitResource(String timestamp,
                                 Resource revisited,
                                 boolean withHeader)
                                          throws IOException
        Create a test revisit record referring Resource revisited.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - CDX-style 14digit timestamp
        revisited - Capture being revisited (must be a WarcResource or ClassCastException will be the result)
        withHeader - true unless you want to emulate old implementation where revisit record had no HTTP headers.
        Returns:
        new Resource object
        Throws:
        IOException - for unexpected I/O error building payload

      • setupCaptures

        protected CaptureSearchResults setupCaptures(int closestIndex,
                                 Resource... resources)
                                      throws Exception
        setup mocks with resources.
        • Call setupCaptures(ResourceIndex, ResourceStore, int, Resource...)
        • Set up replay so as to return closest from getClosest.
        • Set up resourceIndex so as to return results from query(wbRequest)

        Note: wbRequest must be set up before calling this method, or ResourceIndex will not return expected search result set.

        Parameters:
        closestIndex - zero-based index into resources
        resources - resources
        Returns:
        CaptureSearchResults populated with CaptureSearchResult objects.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • setupCaptures

        public static CaptureSearchResults setupCaptures(ResourceIndex resourceIndex,
                                 ResourceStore resourceStore,
                                 int closestIndex,
                                 Resource... resources)
                                          throws Exception
        given a sequence of WarcResources,
        • build CaptureSearchResults, filled with CaptureSearchResult instances, which have auto-generated unique filename and offset of 0. this is necessary for equality (see AccessPointTest.CaptureSearchResultMatcher).
        • setup ResourceStore mock to return Resource for each CaptureSearchResult.
        • if closestIndex >= 0, set corresponding CaptureSearchResult's closest flag.

        It's left as caller's responsibility to setup ResourceIndex.query(WaybackRequest) mock to return CaptureSearchResults returned by this method.

        Parameters:
        resourceIndex - ResourceIndex mock
        resourceStore - ResourceStore mock, can be null
        closestIndex - 0-based index of resource to be marked as closest
        resources - sequence of WarcResources
        Returns:
        CaptureSearchResults populated with CaptureSearchResult objects.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • expectUrlIndexQuery

        protected void expectUrlIndexQuery()
                            throws Exception
        setup expected call to ResourceIndex.query(WaybackRequest), returning empty UrlSearchResults.

        This is sufficient for most cases, as AccessPoint is not concerned with UrlSearchResult, but simply passes it to query renderer.

        Note: set up wbRequest before calling this method.

        Throws:
        Exception - declared, but will never be thrown

        public void testHandleRequest_Replay_1()

      • testHandleRequest_MissingRevisitPayload

        public void testHandleRequest_MissingRevisitPayload()
                                             throws Exception
        handleReplay() is supposed to throw ResourceNotAvailableException when it cannot find a replay-able capture for a request. This is a test for one of such "capture not found" case: revisited record cannot found in the capture search results, and only other non-revisit resource available is a self-redirect. This is rather a corner case. handlReplay() shall throw ResourceNotAvailableException.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • testMemento_replay_exactCapture

        public void testMemento_replay_exactCapture()
                                     throws Exception
        test of Memento-furnished response to URL-M (Memento). Memento Specification states that URL-M response
        • MUST NOT have "Vary: accept-datetime"
        • MUST have "Memento-Datetime"
        • MUST have "Link" header with at least a URI-R as "original" relation.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • testMemento_replay_nearbyCapture

        public void testMemento_replay_nearbyCapture()
                                      throws Exception
        Test of Memento-furnished response to replay request for non-archived timestamp. This is not strictly a URL-M (as far as I understand). Wayback returns intermediate resource to URI-M. Memento Specification states the response
        • MUST NOT have "Vary: accept-datetime" header (this is the key difference from redirect from URI-G; see below)
        • MUST NOT have "Memento-Datetime" header
        • MUST have "Link" header, which MUST have at least "original" relation link. "timegate", "timemap" and "memento" relation type links MAY be provided.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • testMementoTimegate

        public void testMementoTimegate()
                         throws Exception
        Test of Memento-furnished response to Timegate (URI-G). Memento Specification states the response
        • MUST have "Vary: accept-datetime" header
        • MUST NOT have "Memento-Datetime" header
        • MUST have "Link" header, which MUST have at least "original" relation link. "timegate", "timemap" and "memento" relation type links MAY be provided.
        Throws:
        Exception
